    {
      "id": "6cf2217e5ca85f462aba70269ddbdca5322539b8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-11-17 00:27:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nAm I misunderstanding or shouldn't there be a corresponding pruning of the ldiskfs autoconf macros from lustre/build?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "88deb101637d2c6080edac7ae426848cd601a9a4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-17 01:07:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nBrian, could you be more specific please?\n\nLustre will need build/autoconf/lustre-build-ldiskfs.m4 as long as we support ldiskfs in lustre.  The vast majority of what is in there is to support building AGAINST ldiskfs, not to actually build ldiskfs itself.  I removed a couple of things that are obviously no longer needed.\n\nBut if you spot something more that it no longer required, please do point it out.  I am happy to take more out.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "dafe5a665a0ca05b875ec2d1b2a0ea4f2c95608b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 116,
        "name": "Brian J. Murrell",
        "email": "brian.murrell@intel.com",
        "username": "brian",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-11-20 13:08:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nChris,\n\nAs you were.  I saw what I missed the first time around.\n\nI can't +1 for the general concept (that will take somebody who has a better view of the bigger picture -- like Andreas) but the implementation looks fine.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "8fa7f74d05d987d4fb0bfccbe7d74dc5a0f73d55",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-11-21 20:40:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(25 inline comments)\n\nWhile I understand that a lot of cleanup can be done post-split (e.g. removing obsolete ext3 checks in the ldiskfs scripts and other things that are unused _after_ the split), I don't like the idea of cloning the problems in the original scripts into two places.  Now those problems have to be found and fixed twice.\n\nI'd prefer to have a patch to clean up style/obsolete issues the common files first, and then have a patch like this to copy the common files into two places.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "f593c0847f85eafeb190b2084f989019283f662f",
      "author": {
